      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The libertarian view of digital property rights is rooted in the idea that private property rights, as established by the 5th Amendment, extend to digital platforms and online content, just as they do to physical property. This means that private platforms have the right to set their own terms of service and moderation policies, free from government interference, as long as they're not violating any laws. The concept of \"digital property rights\" is closely tied to the idea of \"cyber-libertarianism,\" which argues that online expression and digital assets are entitled to the same protections as physical property, including the right to be free from government seizure or coercion.",
      "source": "target",
